Explanation:

The problem requires counting the number of even and odd bits in a binary representation of a number. We can solve this problem using bitwise operations. The algorithm uses a while loop to iterate until the number becomes 0. In each iteration, it performs a bitwise AND operation with 1 to clear all the set bits and then increments the count of even and odd bits. Finally, it adds the counts to the result vector. The time complexity is O(log(n)) due to the while loop, and the space complexity is O(1) as we only use a constant amount of space for the result vector.

